.@realDonaldTrump is walking away from good-faith negotiations for #COVID19 relief.   He's walking away from his responsibilities as a leader.   And when the American people needed a President most - he's walking away from us. https://t.co/6Wb8zOAQB7
I want to reiterate that we as individuals must stay vigilant by wearing our masks washing our hands and maintaining social distance and as a nation must work together to fight this virus.
While I am fortunate to receive this news my heart is with the over 7 million Americans that have contracted COVID-19 and friends and families of 200000 that passed away.
I have just received word that my COVID-19 test from this morning came back negative. I want to thank all of the Delawareans who reached out to me today sending me prayers and well-wishes.

After President Trump’s announcement that he and the First Lady have tested positive for COVID-19 and given my recent travels to Ohio for the first Presidential Debate I was tested for COVID-19 this morning and will be self-isolating as I await the results of my test. https://t.co/2ldwXIk4Wa

As #COVID19 cases rise in Delaware please be sure to stay vigilant and take every precaution to keep you and your family healthy. Wear a mask stay 6 feet apart and wash your hands often. https://t.co/fDU0nSHKEN

The Jobs and Justice Act addresses the disproportionate impact #COVID19 has had on Black Americans and provides funding for expanded testing contact tracing and treatment for those who need it most.   I am proud to support #JobsandJustice2020. https://t.co/f3xp01kg0O
Starting today #COVID19 testing will be done at fixed locations throughout Delaware.  Visit https://t.co/SbcVMframY to find a location.

This #LaborDay Weekend please be sure to wash your hands wear your mask and stay at least 6 feet away from other people. Have a fun and safe weekend without contributing to the spread of COVID-19. https://t.co/FqDmoP3Bzf
As part of National Health Center Week I joined @westsidehealth to discuss the critical role health centers play in responding to the #COVID19 pandemic. #NHCW2020 https://t.co/04KfMAwoFb
#COVID19 has had devastating health & economic impacts on women & families—especially women of color.

As we celebrate 55 years of the #VotingRightsAct our work to ensure every American’s access to the ballot isn’t over.   Congress must pass the John R. Lewis Voting Rights Act and give states the resources they need to #ProtectOurVote amid the COVID-19 crisis. #VRA55

Only 1/3 of the 12 million jobs women have lost due to #COVID19 have returned & women of color have been hit hardest. We can’t leave them behind.   @HouseDemocrats passed the #HeroesAct to extend federal unemployment assistance. The Senate needs to act now.

Too many families across the country will face eviction due to the financial strain of #COVID19 when the federal moratorium expires tomorrow. With COVID cases and unemployment continuing to rise we must extend the moratorium. #RentReliefNow https://t.co/wJfqNJXck4

The #COVID19 pandemic has further exposed what we already knew - mental health disparities among communities of color are growing as they face growing uncertainty over health money and their futures. #HEAA2020
If you’re headed to the beaches this weekend please remember to wear a mask and social distance. #MaskUpDE https://t.co/36qzyyxN2X

#ICYMI Over 50 organizations support my bill the Quit Because of COVID-19 Act. There has never been a more critical time to help #Medicaid and #CHIP beneficiaries access cessation services to quit using tobacco and reduce the risk of #COVID19 complications.
I want to thank @SecAzar for giving Nanticoke this award and the health care heroes on the frontlines at Nanticoke who continue to do the hard work of fighting COVID-19.

@ChooseNanticoke has been on the frontlines of the #COVID19 pandemic here in Delaware. Like many small rural hospitals across the country Nanticoke has faced an unprecedented drain on their resources in recent months. https://t.co/LxWG9U9yOB

Today marks 4 months since a national emergency for #COVID19 was announced.   122 days. @realDonaldTrump & his @WhiteHouse still don’t have a national testing strategy.   Rather than attacking Dr. Fauci perhaps the President should talk to him. https://t.co/6KzSFg9q01

As we continue our economic recovery from #COVID19 I've been thinking a lot about the #FutureofWork.   It was great to join my friend @AFitzpayne & the @AspenInstitute to talk about the #FutureofWork & a host of other important issues. https://t.co/XySG30vK4z

Thank you Amanda for sharing Nick’s story with us. It‘s a tragic reminder of how serious #COVID19 is. Let his memory serve to remind us that the LEAST we can do for each other is to wear a mask. My heart is with you Elvis & the rest of Nick’s family. https://t.co/fVLzD63UBR

Today the House of Representatives voted to extend the Paycheck Protection Program until August 8. As #COVID19 cases continue to rise small businesses need this funding now more than ever to keep their businesses running.

Tune in at 1:00 PM to join a virtual discussion w/ @AspenFutureWork & @AspenFSP on the economy and the labor workforce – and what responses look like in a post-#COVID19 world. I’m thankful to be included in such an important conversation.  Join here: https://t.co/w3Zm6849H1

Enhancing Medicaid coverage of tobacco cessation services will give Medicaid beneficiaries the best chance to quit successfully potentially help them avoid the most serious consequences of #COVID19 and reduce health costs associated with smoking.

Looking to quit smoking? Now is as good a time as ever. #COVID19 is an acute respiratory virus that attacks the lungs. That's why today I introduced the Quit Because of #COVID19 Act. https://t.co/5gki5F7aeh

As @EnergyCommerce held a hearing on the disproportionate impacts of #COVID19 on #EJ communities Geroge Floyd was being laid to rest and was heavy on my heart.  It's time for all of us - myself included - to hold up a mirror reflect and ask what can we do differently? https://t.co/drNXJmJC1l

If we do not take action we could soon face prescription drug shortages on top of the #COVID19 pandemic.    The #HeroesAct includes provisions from my bill requiring drug manufacturers to create a risk mitigation plan. https://t.co/XA3UuvbfOY

100000 Americans have now been lost to #COVID19. Let us all remember that these are not just numbers – not just statistics.   These were 100000 mothers fathers sisters brothers and friends. They left behind families and loved ones. We must never forget them. https://t.co/6yt08PaLKz

During a pandemic families should not have to worry about whether or not they will have running water.   The #HeroesAct would put an end to water shutoffs nationally during the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/yhhtNb32kB

#COVID19 is shining a light on the disproportionate and cumulative impacts pollution has on low income and communities of color.

This morning I had the opportunity to speak with Dr. Anthony Fauci on a call hosted by the @NewDemCoalition. I'm grateful for his expertise & guidance as we discussed health disparities and the role that they have played during the #COVID19 crisis.
Cost should never be a barrier to #COVID19 treatment.  The #HeroesAct includes my bill to ensure patients have no out-of-pocket costs for any #COVID19 treatment they receive. https://t.co/tWgG80CfDp

Today’s a big day. The House is back in session to vote on the #HeroesAct - a bold and necessary step in our fight against #COVID19. From testing to tracing to treatment - this package takes the bold action we need now. #ForThePeople https://t.co/oj6rfQsBR8
